findings*
# Ignore all files in the findings directory
findings/*

__*
# Ignore all files that start with double underscores | General pattern for temporary or generated files, or test files with no real value to be tracked in version control.

_test*
*_test*
_tests*
/tests/*
# Ignore all files that start with _test | Common pattern for test files that may not need to be tracked in version control.
# Ignore all files that start with _tests | Similar to the above, but for files that may have a plural form.
# Ignore all files in the tests directory | This is a common pattern for ignoring an entire directory that contains test files, which may not need to be tracked in version control.

__pycache__/
# Ignore the __pycache__ directory | This is a common pattern for ignoring the directory that contains compiled Python files, which are generated automatically and do not need to be tracked in version control.

*.log
# Ignore all log files | This is a common pattern for ignoring log files, which are often generated during development and do not need to be tracked in version control.
*logs.txt
*logs.*

*.env
# Ignore all .env files | This is a common pattern for ignoring environment variable files, which may contain sensitive information and should not be tracked in version control.
*.tmp
# Ignore all temporary files | This is a common pattern for ignoring temporary files, which are often generated during development and do not need to be tracked in version control.
*.bak
# Ignore all backup files | This is a common pattern for ignoring backup files, which are often generated during development and do not need to be tracked in version control.
*.swp
# Ignore all swap files | This is a common pattern for ignoring swap files, which are often generated by text editors and do not need to be tracked in version control.
.DS_Store	
# Ignore .DS_Store files | This is a common pattern for ignoring .DS_Store files, which are generated by macOS and do not need to be tracked in version control.
Thumbs.db

*backups*
# Ignore all files that contain "backups" in their name | This is a common pattern for ignoring backup files, which may be generated during development and do not need to be tracked in version control.

*.exe
# Ignore all executable files | This is a common pattern for ignoring executable files, which may be generated during development and do not need to be tracked in version control.
*.dll
# Ignore all dynamic link library files | This is a common pattern for ignoring DLL files, which may be generated during development and do not need to be tracked in version control.
*.so
# Ignore all shared object files | This is a common pattern for ignoring shared object files, which may be generated during development and do not need to be tracked in version control.